title: The Game Interview: Fatherhood, Durk vs Youngboy, Losing His Father, Gay Rights & More
description:
Unexpectedly candid #TheGame interview, where he talks about fatherhood, his parents, his kids, having an addictive personality, Joe Budden, Durk, Von, Crip Mac, and more.

-----
00:00 Intro
2:30 "I chose to be real with my fans and my family, if I wanted to be a billionaire, I would be"
5:02 "I can walk away from music I wanted to, I can get a bag anywhere"
11:10 Wouldn't really advise young rappers not to beef on their songs if that's their way to go about things
17:28 "If you have personal beef, just know there are consequences especially when it's negative"
20:58 "My new album is gonna be number 1"
22:45 Rappers passing away leaving their kids behind
26:40 "I'm on some love and peace thing"
28:49 Game on losing in father, kinda took his place within the family, being a responsible dad
37:40 His mom's health is frail
41:37 Hates dropping his kids at school and leaving them with strangers and is scared of school sh____
47:44 Game wants Brittney Griner outta jail, tired of marching for the same issues: "It's just hate, people hate people they don't even know why it's just systemic"
50:08 Obama playlist
56:25 Kids saying that Durk didn't slide for King Von, Game reacts
1:00:45 Game has nothing against gay people, has gay friends
1:05:00 Game doubts that Saucy Santana had a BBL
1:09:17 Lena used to have a huge crush on Game
1:10:35 Game says if he and 50 never beef who knows what could've happened
1:12:18 Being drunk during the Drink Champs interview, Nore says Game was drinking water
1:14:09 Game moved the album date like Detox, says it's because of sample clearances
1:21:48 Game addresses the scandal with Pricilla
1:24:01 Adam and Game debate on how life would be if their ___ were chopped off
1:35:06 Game and Joe beef: "Joe ain't a threat to nobody"
1:40:25 Game asks Adam about Lena and p___
1:43;45 Doesn't like lean and tries shrooms sometimes
1:49:40 Game says he wouldn't recognize Stitches if he saw him
1:51:00 S/O Crip Mac

-----
